   <titleInfo>
      <title>Aftermath of the "Million Dollar Fire"</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>View of Gay Street after Knoxville's "Million Dollar Fire." This fire, which occurred on April 7, 1897, started in the Hotel Knox and consumed most of the 400 block of Gay Street before being stopped at the Sanford, Chamberlain &amp; Albers Company Building with a firewall. The fire killed three people and a rare white mule (visiting Knoxville with an itinerant circus). The mule's ghost is said to have started a number of small fires in the area since.</abstract>
